    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-24T08:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-24T08:35:00-05:00" n="628"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d628">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51/582: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-24T17:00:00+03:25"
                            >July 24, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>770. Millspaugh furnishes following replies to numbered paragraphs of
                    Department’s 357, July 22.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>It is again confirmed that in event of a dollar loan being obtained
                        proceeds would be used for issuing rial currency.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Yes.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Reserve against notes issued since November 19, 1942 is 100 percent in
                        gold and/or dollars or sterling. No change in this reserve requirement is
                        contemplated.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>Yes. Bank is required to maintain 40% ratio between liquid assets (in the
                        form of rial notes, gold, silver, free foreign currencies or 15 days’ bills)
                        and immediate liabilities.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>No.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
